```

**Mistral Small 3.2** (different - has `[CALL_ID]`):
- Uses `[INST]/[/INST]` for user messages
- Has `[CALL_ID]` marker for tool call IDs
- Falls through to autoparser (not specialized)

**Ministral-3 Message Transformation** (Lines 831-866):
```cpp
// Input: standard messages with content/reasoning_content
// Output: messages with content arrays containing typed blocks

auto adjusted_messages = json::array();
for (const auto & msg : inputs.messages) {
    auto content = json::array();

    // Add reasoning as "thinking" block
    if (msg.contains("reasoning_content")) {
        content.push_back({
            { "type", "thinking" },
            { "thinking", msg.at("reasoning_content") }
        });
    }

    // Add content as "text" block
    if (msg.contains("content")) {
        if (msg.at("content").is_string()) {
            content.push_back({
                { "type", "text" },
                { "text", msg.at("content") }
            });
        } else if (msg.at("content").is_array()) {
            // Already array, insert as-is
            auto blocks = msg.at("content");
            content.insert(content.end(), blocks.begin(), blocks.end());
        }
    }

    auto adjusted = msg;
    adjusted["content"] = content;
    adjusted.erase("reasoning_content");
    adjusted_messages.push_back(adjusted);
}
```

