# Plan: Add `mistral-instruct-v3` Specialized Chat Template Handler

## Context

llama.cpp has a two-tier chat template system: specialized C++ handlers for known template families (better reliability and output parsing), and a generic differential autoparser fallback. The Mistral Instruct v0.3 format uses `[INST]`/`[/INST]` markers and prepends system messages into the first user turn, with `</s>` after assistant turns — but has **no** `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` token (unlike Ministral 3). Currently it falls through to the autoparser; adding a dedicated handler makes it explicit, reliable, and easier to maintain.

## Critical Files

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `common/chat.cpp` | All specialized handler implementations + auto-detection function |
| `common/chat.h` | Declares `common_chat_try_specialized_template` (**read-only, no changes allowed**) |

## Implementation — Two changes, one file (`common/chat.cpp`)

### Change 1 — New handler function

**Insert before line 1519** (immediately before `namespace workaround {`).

```cpp
static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(
        const common_chat_template &          tmpl,
        const autoparser::generation_params & inputs) {
    common_chat_params data;

    // Mistral Instruct v0.3 prepends the system message to the first user turn
    // inside the [INST] block. Build an adjusted message list that merges a
    // leading system message into the first user message before template rendering.
    auto adjusted_messages = inputs.messages;
    if (!adjusted_messages.empty() && adjusted_messages.front().value("role", "") == "system") {
        std::string sys_content = adjusted_messages.front().value("content", "");
        adjusted_messages.erase(adjusted_messages.begin());
        if (!adjusted_messages.empty() && adjusted_messages.front().value("role", "") == "user") {
            std::string user_content = adjusted_messages.front().value("content", "");
            adjusted_messages.front()["content"] = sys_content + "\n\n" + user_content;
        }
    }

    data.prompt            = common_chat_template_direct_apply_impl(tmpl, inputs, /* messages_override = */ adjusted_messages);
    data.format            = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_PEG_NATIVE;
    data.supports_thinking = false;
    data.preserved_tokens  = { "[INST]", "[/INST]", "</s>" };

    auto parser = build_chat_peg_parser([&](common_chat_peg_builder & p) {
        return p.literal(inputs.generation_prompt) + p.content(p.rest());
    });

    data.parser = parser.save();

    return data;
}
```

**Key design decisions:**
- System message is merged into the first user message with `\n\n` separator (matching Mistral's documented format).
- `common_chat_template_direct_apply_impl` is called with the adjusted messages (pattern used by every other specialized handler: Ministral 3, LFM2.5, GigaChatV3, etc.).
- Parser is content-only (`p.rest()`): Mistral Instruct v0.3 has no special tool-call token syntax, so no grammar/trigger machinery is needed.
